The paper deals with the verification of stateful protocols using symbolic models and automated analysis. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it involves cryptography and protocol analysis. The paper also uses formal methods and logic (cs.LO) to establish computational soundness results. The use of the applied \pi-calculus and CoSP framework suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the differences between the semantics of the two languages, which could be relevant to formal language theory (cs.FL).
